title: JENA-2097: Bad URIs are parser warnings
body:
JENA-2097 shows two things:

1. checking urn:uuid was broken (4.0.0 adds checking of UUIDs).
1. IRI problems should be warnings (parsing does not stop).

Only IRI syntax that is broken to the point where `<>` can't be matched or impossible characters (e.g. space) are used should be a parse-stop error as it was in jena 3.17.0, especially for N-Triples.

To this end, add a test suite `TestIRIxRIOT` that has test cases for all the situations, checking the numbers of errors and warning produced for the new IRIx abstraction use in RIOT parsing.

Relative IRIs are now a special case with their own exception `RelativeIRIException`. Some formats (N-Triples when not strict) accept them. Turtle always resolves them (and there is always a base) unless specific low-level setup is done when it can be a parse-stop error.

Behaviour in normal use should be like 3.17.0 with only possible changes of ERROR to WARN in messages. Behaviour in detailed setup for Turtle now has test cases.

title: JENA-2088: Quad execution. Rework the basic graph pattern execution. Code clean up.
body:
This PR is code maintenance triggered by [JENA-2088](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JENA-2088): Quad execution, node Solver and code rework.

It reworks the code for basic graph pattern solving in ARQ (i.e. for Nodes, not TDB internal IDs) into the same style as TDB. This means that providing the same features of union default and filter is done in the same style and that timeout abort is handled the same way.

Old classes used for BGP solving is deprecated,not removed.

Much of the code is not "new" so much as TDB code backported to work on `Nodes`.

Includes other work:

* [JENA-2082](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JENA-2082): Single test manifest runner.
* [JENA-2090](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JENA-2090): Add Graph.stream
* [JENA-2091](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JENA-2091): Add methods Graph.add(s,p,o) and .delete(s,p,o)

What is included is switching on quad+node execution. There is an `OpExecutorQuad` but it is not active.

The intention is switch to have TIM to use this quad execution.

Then all the storage datasets (TIM, TDB1 TDB2) have the same feature set provided in the same style.

  • Increased the aggressiveness of Guava 30.1's warning log message for running guava-android under a Java 7 VM. (Android VMs are unaffected.) We have tried to make the warning as safe as possible, but anytime a common library logs, especially as aggressively as we do in this new release, there is the potential for NullPointerException or even deadlock. title: JENA-2049: Binding improvements
body:
While this is a big PR, most of the files changed are because all uses of binding in Jena have been converted to the new code. The old way (`BindingMap`) still works.

While making these changes, the process was to change some files to new style, then run the tests suite so that if behaviour changed, it was simpler to track down whether it was the translation of the usage code or the binding sub-system implementation.

The old style is still there in `BindingFactory` as deprecated static methods to smooth migration. The original classes in case for code using the classes directly and not via the factory.

The key new class is `BindingBuilder`.

The main change in code is `BindingMap BindingFactory.create()` becomes `BindingBuilder Binding.builder()` and the effects of that.

title: Bump ver.jetty from 9.4.35.v20201120 to 10.0.0
body:
Bumps `ver.jetty` from 9.4.35.v20201120 to 10.0.0. Updates `jetty-servlet` from 9.4.35.v20201120 to 10.0.0
Release notes

Sourced from jetty-servlet's releases.

10.0.0

Eclipse Jetty 10.x Highlights

  • Jetty 10.x has a minimum Java requirement of Java 11.
  • Jetty 10.x modules are proper JPMS modules with module-info.class.
  • Jetty 10.x supports the following technology specs (from the Jakarta EE 8 effort):
    • javax.servlet - 4.0.1
    • javax.servlet.jsp - 2.2
    • javax.servlet.jsp.jstl - 1.2
    • javax.el - 3.0.0
    • javax.websocket - 1.1
  • Jetty 10.x will be the last major version of Jetty to support the javax.servlet namespace.
    Use Jetty 11.x for the updated jakarta.servlet namespace.

Important Changes

  • Classic jetty logging facade has been replaced with slf4j-api usage
  • There is no longer a jetty-distribution, use jetty-home with a proper ${jetty.base} instead.
    See: Operations Guide: Architecture
    • New demo jetty-start module exists to replace the old demo-base functionality.
  • Remove jetty-all uber artifact
  • Managing Configuration within a WebAppContext has a new API.
    (They are now self ordering and do not require knowledge of Jetty internals to use successfully)
  • Complete WebSocket refactoring, those using the Jetty APIs or embedded-jetty will need to update their code.
    • Support for WebSocket over HTTP/2 (client and server)
  • Jetty HttpClient has been improved.
    • Supports dynamic protocol upgrade (http/2 and http/1.1).
